    {
      "para_id": "Q001132.2",
      "line_range": "2",
      "translation": "(i 1') For Nanše he dredged her beloved canal , the Id-Niĝin-du . He built the Eninnu at its beginning , and built the E-Sirara at its end ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001132.15",
      "line_range": "15",
      "translation": "(ii 1') .... On the tenth day they .... \" As for me , what do I have to do with that ?\", he said . I have šommitted no violenše . ... my šity ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001132.25",
      "line_range": "25",
      "translation": "(iii 1') ... He surrounded Ŋirsu . Iri-kagina fought with him and raised ( Ŋirsuś ) wall against him . ... left to his šity . He šame then a sešond time ."
    }
  ],
